{"id": 225020942, "title": "Man 'covered in blood' after horror dog attack in Scots town", "text": "A man was rushed to hospital after being attacked by a dog in Airdrie. The incident occurred around 10.40pm on Tuesday, May 28, with emergency services quickly arriving at the South Bridge Street area following reports of a disturbance. A 40 year old man was discovered injured and required treatment at hospital. An eyewitness told Glasgow Live that the man was \"covered in blood\" following the late-night incident. A 33 year old woman has been charged under the Dangerous Dogs Act and the Staffordshire Bull Terrier involved was put down, police confirmed. A spokesperson for Police Scotland said: \"Around 10.40pm on Tuesday, 28 May, we received a report of a disturbance in the South Bridge Street area of Airdrie.\" \"A 40-year-old man was bitten by a dog and attended Monklands Hospital for treatment.\" \"A 33-year-old woman has been charged in connection with the Dangerous Dogs Act.\", reports Glasgow Live. \"The dog, a Staffordshire Bull Terrier, was euthanised.\" Don't miss the latest news from around Scotland and beyond - Sign up to our daily newsletter here.", "summary": "The incident happened at around 10.40pm on Tuesday, May 28, with emergency services rushing to the South Bridge Street area of Airdrie following reports of a disturbance.", "url": "https://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/news/uk-world-news/man-covered-blood-after-horror-32916968", "image": "https://i2-prod.dailyrecord.co.uk/news/uk-world-news/article32916949.ece/ALTERNATES/s1200/442457815_3638462496470158_7915032869802734979_n.jpg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-05-29 12:58:18", "author": "Chiara Pollock", "authors": ["Chiara Pollock"], "language": "en", "source_country": "gb", "sentiment": -0.332}